react router dom
lucide-react

react hot toast = notification

react-player = videos

clerk = for authentication
npm install @clerk/clerk-react


1. <UserButton> — the user avatar & dropdown
This renders the authenticated user’s profile avatar

When clicked, it opens a dropdown menu

Provided by Clerk

By default, this menu contains items like:

Manage account

Sign out


2. <UserButton.MenuItems> — extend the dropdown
This component lets you add custom menu items

Anything inside it appears inside the user dropdown

You are extending, not replacing, Clerk’s menu

3. <UserButton.Action> — custom clickable action
What each prop does
label
label="My Bookings"


Text shown in the menu

labelIcon
labelIcon={<TicketPlus width={15} />}


Icon displayed next to the label

TicketPlus is from lucide-react

width={15} controls icon size

onClick
onClick={() => navigate('/my-bookings')}


Executes when the menu item is clicked

Uses React Router’s navigate

Redirects the user to /my-bookings



